{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SZgCcKP3qhp3VEeam3G7a4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * reactions.cu -- K_Reactions kernel: per-particle state machine for\n     3→ * phase transitions, combustion, corrosion, and gas lifetime.\n     4→ *\n     5→ * No neighbor loop -- each thread processes one particle independently.\n     6→ * Reads exposure accumulators from Step1, checks temperature and exposure\n     7→ * thresholds, and modifies material type, behavior class, temperature,\n     8→ * health, lifetime, and velocity as needed.\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Runs on SORTED arrays, between Step1 (which computes exposure) and\n    11→ * Step2 (which computes forces). Modifications to sorted_packed_info\n    12→ * flow through Step2 and Integrate naturally.\n    13→ *\n    14→ * Constant memory used:\n    15→ *   c_sim       -- SimParams (dt)\n    16→ *   c_materials -- MaterialProps[32] (for looking up current material props)\n    17→ */\n    18→\n    19→#include \"common.cuh\"\n    20→\n    21→/* ======================================================================\n    22→ * Material IDs (must match materials.py)\n    23→ * ====================================================================== */\n    24→\n    25→#define MAT_DEAD       0\n    26→#define MAT_STONE      1\n    27→#define MAT_WATER      5\n    28→#define MAT_OIL        6\n    29→#define MAT_LAVA       7\n    30→#define MAT_WOOD       9\n    31→#define MAT_ICE       11\n    32→#define MAT_STEAM     12\n    33→#define MAT_FIRE      14\n    34→#define MAT_GUNPOWDER 15\n    35→\n    36→/* ======================================================================\n    37→ * Reaction thresholds\n    38→ * ====================================================================== */\n    39→\n    40→#define ICE_MELT_TEMP         273.0f   // ICE -> WATER above this\n    41→#define LAVA_SOLIDIFY_TEMP    900.0f   // LAVA -> STONE below this\n    42→#define WATER_BO